Level: 2
Range: 30 meters
Duration: 1 round / level
Casting Time: 2
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: none

This spell turns the target of the spell completely invisible to inanimate items. As for the Major Invisibility spell, the recipient of the spell can take any action, including offensive nature, without becoming visible for inanimate items; the latters can not see or detect in any way as long as he is covered by the spell.~
@20221 = ~Invisible to inanimate items~

@2023 = ~Anti chicken turning~
@2024 = ~Anti chicken turning (Normalization)
Level: 2
Range: 0
Duration: instantaneous
Casting Time: 2
Area of Effect: the caster
Saving Throw: none

This spell allows the mage accidentally turned into chicken recover his original shape. Designed by a very gifted apprentice named Melican, (at least that's what the official version assumes), the spell is not perfect and needs some luck to be useful.
First, one must be able to cast the spell in the shape of chicken. Second, one must pass a saving throw against polymorph to regain the original shape, otherwise the spell sprays the mage. Use cautiously then.
Note: This spell is meant to help a mage turned into a chicken. No one knows the effect if cast by a non-turned mage, Melican did not bother to test it under human shape.~

@2031 = ~Aiding-Watermelon~
@2032 = ~Aiding-Watermelon (Transportation)
Level: 3
Range: contact
Duration: 8 hours
Casting Time: 3
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: none

The goal of the spell is helping the target to carry more watermelons. The spell does not affect the weight or size of the watermelons carried by the target, but help him carrying more.
The number of additional watermelons that can be carried depends upon the class of the enchanted character.
Barbarian  +1D8 watermelons
Fighter / Paladin / Ranger  +1D6 watermelons
Monk / Priest  +1D4+1 watermelons
Bard / Thief  +1D4 watermelons
Mage / Wizard  +1D2 watermelons~

@2033 = ~Aura against the Dishes~
@2034 = ~Aura against the Dishes (Protection)
Level: 3
Range: 0
Duration: 2 rounds / level
Casting Time: 3
Area of Effect: 1 meter around the caster
Saving Throw: none

The mage is surrounded by an aura that protects him from the dishes launched against him. As long as the fate lasts, any plate moving penetrating the perimeter of 1 meter around the mage is immediately turned into a sugar pancake.
The spell does not stop the pancake, although the latter is affected by weight and shape change of the projectile.
The spell targets only dishes (any size, material or weight) and does not turn glasses, jugs, pots, anything that is launched during the fight or domestic dispute.~

@2035 = ~Pressing Calling of Slippers~
@2036 = ~Pressing Calling of Slippers (Confortation)
Level: 3
Range: Special
Duration: instantaneous
Casting Time: 3
Area of Effect: caster
Saving Throw: none

This spell makes appear at the feet of the caster the favorite slippers, so he can spend an evening at home wearing his slippers.
The spell is infallible, will fetch the slippers wherever they are, even if they are saddled under or in a pocket dimension.
They will appear on the pavement at the foot of mage, replacing others if there are other shoes, and stay there until the mage chooses to remove his shoes.~
@20361 = ~Squirrel Slippers.~
@20362 = ~These are your slippers. They are very comfortable.~

