@2053 = ~Transformation of rock into stone~
@2054 = ~Transformation of rock into stone (Restatement)
Level: 5
Range: 30 meters
Duration: Permanent
Casting Time: 6
Area of Effect: 2m3 / Level
Saving Throw: Negate

This spell transforms the rock in nature state (that is to say not worked) in an amount of non-magical stone. The rock chosen as target is entitled to a saving throw if it is intact, not if it is cracked or naturally altered in some kind of way. If the rock misses or does not take a saving throw, it is irreparably turned into stone.~

@2061 = ~Time Tranel~
@2062 = ~Time Travel (Seclusion)
Level: 6
Range: -
Duration: instantaneous
Casting Time: 1 hour
Area of Effect: caster
Saving Throw: none

This spell allows travelling in the future. To cast it, the mage must have a laboratory equipped with a closet. He must be cloistered in the closet for the duration of the spell (1 hour).
Coming out of that closet, he will be projected into the future, about an hour after the start of the cast.
This spell is not reversible and therefore can not travel into the past.~
@20621 = ~*Casting Canceled* Oops, I'm not in a cupboard of my laboratory.~

@2063 = ~Personal Resurrection~
@2064 = ~Personal Resurrection (Resuscitation)
Level: 6
Range: 0
Duration: instantaneous
Casting Time: 8
Area of Effect: caster
Saving Throw: none

You're dead. No problem. Cast this spell and you resurrect, in full possession of your items and soon resume the fight, with spells that you had at the time of your death memorized. Each personal resurrection costs you 2 life points that are permanently lost.
This spell can affect a person really dead only, which excluds the undead. It can not affect a mage who has exceeded his life expectancy (age death).~
@20641 = ~ Unlucky !! This spell was to be cast by a dead to bring him back to life. A living which casts it, causes the opposite effect, that makes sense!~

@2071 = ~Cleaning Silt Invocation~ // Unable to do, parameter "only inside" nonexistent.
@2072 = ~Cleaning Silt Invocation (Cleaning Up)
Level: 7
Range: Visual field of the caster
Duration: 1 day / level
Casting Time: 6
Area of ??Effect: Special
Saving Throw: none

This spell summons a cleaning silt, amorphous creature who will rid any enclosed place from dirt that prevails. The silt is dirtivous, it ingests and disintegrates dust, dirt and debris. It does not fight, and if it has to, it will just start throwing bactericidal soaps over its attackers to wash them if they are dirty.

This spell can be cast only indoors; the cleaning silt does not stand daylight, it melts in 1D4 rounds if exposed (it can still bear to pass a window, if it does not stand there).

Attention: some uncertain gossips report that a little cleaning silt would have fully cleaned the great library of Kalieshira, leaving en empty tower as cleaned building.~

@20111 = ~Super Heroism~
@20112 = ~Super Heroism (Evolution)
Level: 11
Range: 0
Duration: Permanent
Casting Time: 5 rounds
Area of Effect: caster
Saving Throw: none

After casting, the mage finally won the super haste power. The power of the spell gives exceptional haste, greater than the speed of light. The mage that has such power can not even be followed by a god; he is no longer plaything of fate. He is beyond.~
@201121 = ~The magic of the spell worked and makes you a superman. You live hasted now. If time seems to have stopped, this is only an optical illusion: the rest of the multiverse will take 1,000 years to make what you can now do in 1 second; this is what makes the world appear as frozen. You also see the world without color, because you are also faster than the photons that make up light.~

@20113 = ~Supreme Teleport~
@20114 = ~Supreme Teleport (Transpose)
Level: 11
Range: -
Duration: Permanent
Casting Time: 5 rounds
Area of Effect: Infinite
Saving Throw: none

To cast this spell, the mage must always be placed in the universe. If he is not there, he can not cast the spell.
If the universe is in range, the mage who casts the spell is instantly teleported thousand light-years to the left, with his clothing, equipment, those who are at his side, the ground on which he places his feet and in short, everything that surrounds him (planet, solar system, galaxy, multiverse). As EVERYTHING moves simultaneously, an unwarned observer might think that nothing has happened. This spell may therefore be spectacular, although it does involve cosmic forces.~

@20115 = ~Dimension Change~
@20116 = ~Dimension Change (Conversion)
Level: 11
Range: 0
Duration: Permanent
Casting Time: 5 rounds
Area of Effect: caster
Saving Throw: none

This spell changes the dimension of the caster. More than a change of plane, it is the structure of the universe that the caster travels that changes. It goes from 2D to 3D dimension. This is a fundamental change providing a new view of things and an almost complete change of known rules which offers to the mage casting this spell. He can only stand up.~
@201161 = ~Now you can quit BG2 and recreate your character in Neverwinter Nights 1 or 2 to enjoy a new 3D world, a different view and improved rules of Dungeon and Dragon 3.5 edition.~





